1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:03,001
In this lesson we will learn to differentiate between homepage display settings and the various templates that come with a block theme.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
In one of our previous sessions we were introduced to page templates, their function, how to edit a template, adding a new template and how to assign a template to a page or post.

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:21,000
In future lessons we will take a closer look at some of these templates individually.

4
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
But let's go ahead and gain a deep understanding of how to use the various templates that come with a block theme and setting your homepage display.

5
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Templates such as the pages template, index template, single posts template, 404 template and all archives template.

6
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
As a reminder WordPress uses templates to create the layout and structure for a page or post.

7
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Let's start by looking at the page template when you make your way to the Site Editor and click on Templates

8
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
you will notice Pages. The page template is the default template and every new page you create will be assigned to this template.

9
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:09,000
You will also possibly see other custom page templates depending on your theme such as page no title, page with sidebar etc.

10
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,000
As you can see the Twenty Twenty-Four theme, the one which I am using, provides four extra custom page templates bottom left, which you could use, edit and assign to single or multiple pages.

11
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
When we open the page template we will see that our header and footer are already in place.

12
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
And then we can open up our List View and select the Group block. And there we will see the Content block or the Post Content block.

13
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
And the Post Content block pulls in the content from pages assigned to this template. Remember we don't add content to the page template.

14
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:02,000
We only provide structure by for example adding a header and a footer.

15
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Next let's return to our templates and discuss the blog home template as well as the index template.

16
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,000
But to do that we have to also discuss the home page display settings.

17
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
So let's make our way to Settings and click on Reading. And then select a static home page and a static blog page.

18
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,000
If you have selected a static home page, all your pages including your home page will be assigned to the page template.

19
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
And if you have selected a static blog page or posts page, your blog or posts page will be assigned to the blog home template.

20
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,000
Let's see this in action. On this website I have installed and activated the Twenty Twenty-Four theme and I have set a static home page and a static blog page.

21
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:59,000
Then we can make our way to Pages and if we open up a homepage we will see it has been assigned to the page template.

22
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:06,000
And if we open up our blog page we will see that this page has been assigned to the blog home template.

23
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,000
And please note you will edit the content and the header and the footer of your blog page or posts page right within the blog home template.

24
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,000
So yes, you will build your entire blog page or posts page within the template.

25
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,000
But what if you have selected your latest posts as your homepage display?

26
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Well, your blog home template will become your homepage.

27
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
If we make our way to the Site Editor, go to pages and at the top we will see our homepage.

28
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
In this case the blog home template and this is also indicated by the home icon on the left.

29
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Here is a very important tip for when you create your navigation menu for your website.

30
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,000
So let's make our way to our main navigation menu and at the moment it's empty.

31
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Then I'll select edit and use the sidebar settings to add my Homepage link.

32
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Here's the tip, add the Home Link block.

33
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
As this means your home navigation menu will go to the home page display you set.

34
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Next let's talk about the index template.

35
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,000
The index template is used as a fall back template for all pages when a more specific template is not defined.

36
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
So it literally means that the index template will be used as a backup template if a theme has not assigned a specific template.

37
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Let's see this in action.

38
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:47,000
On this website I've installed and activated the Tove theme and this theme actually does not have a blog home template.

39
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,000
So if we make our way to Settings and Reading you'll notice I've already set a static home page and posts page.

40
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,000
And if we then go to pages we'll see that our homepage has been assigned to the page template.

41
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:12,000
The same as before. But if we go to our posts page or our blog page we will notice that this page has been assigned to the index template.

42
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,000
The fallback template or the backup template.

43
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Next let's return to our Reading settings and change our homepage display to our latest posts page.

44
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Once saved we can head to the Site Editor and we will see that our index template is now our homepage.

45
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:43,000
As mentioned the index template is merely a fallback template. So it is not advised to use the index template for your homepage or blog page.

46
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:52,000
So what is the best solution?

47
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:55,000
It would be best to add a new template. So when we click on the plus icon next to templates we can add the blog home template if available.

48
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Or add and assign a custom template for our latest posts homepage or static blog page.

49
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
Next we move on to the single posts template.

50
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,000
This template influences the layout of individual posts.

51
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:26,000
Although we don't add content to the single posts template you can change and modify the layout of the template.

52
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,000
For example you can move around theme blocks such as post author, post date, post category, post tag etc.

53
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:44,000
And if you want to allow comments on your site remember to make sure you don't accidentally delete the Comments block.

54
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
The next template we would like to discuss is the 404 template.

55
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
The 404 template steps in when a page isn't found.

56
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Remember there is no page assigned to this template.

57
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,000
If you want your 404 page to have a unique look and feel you can edit the 404 template directly.

58
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:13,000
In this example you will notice I have modified and changed the 404 template to meet my needs and to speak to my customers.

59
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Another template to take note of is the search results template.

60
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:29,000
This template displays when a visitor performs a search on your website.

61
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Here is my coffee shop website and if I type in the word "coffee" and then hit Ssearch I will see all the related posts with this term being displayed.

62
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
And you can of course modify this template and change how search results are displayed.

63
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,000
The next template we will discuss is the all archives template.

64
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:57,000
The all archives template displays groupings of posts by categories, tags or archives such as author, month or year.

65
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:06,000
So for example if you want to see all the posts from a specific category this template will be used.

66
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
You will notice at the top it says archive type and then name.

67
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:19,000
The archive type can be a category, a tag, an author and then of course the name is the name of the post.

68
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:25,000
Let's visit my blog page to see how this works.

69
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:30,000
So firstly I will scroll down to all my posts and then select a post named Texture.

70
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Now below the title we will see the date and then the author and the category namely Art.

71
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:46,000
And then below the text the tag namely Abstract.

72
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,000
So let's go ahead and click on the Art category.

73
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,000
So at the top the archive type is the category and in the name and below that we will see all the posts within the Art category.

74
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,000
Then I will return to the post named Texture and select the author.

75
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,000
And below the archive type 'author' we will view all the posts written by this specific author.

76
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:19,000
And the layout of this page is of course determined by the all archives template which can be modified.

77
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:26,000
But what if you wanted to create a template for a specific category or tag or author?

78
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:33,000
Well you can do that by adding a template.

79
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
So you can click on the Inserter or the plus icon next to templates

80
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:42,000
you can add a template for author archives - for all your authors or for a specific person.

81
00:09:47,000 --> 00:09:50,000
You also have the option to add a category template for all your categories or for individual categories.

82
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:58,000
You can also create a template for date archives or tag archives.

83
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Then you will notice you also have an option to add a new page template

84
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:11,000
or a single item post template. So basically a template for a single post.

85
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:17,000
And at the bottom we'll see we can also add a custom template.

86
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:22,000
A custom template can be manually applied to any post or page.

87
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Another template which you can add is a front page template.

88
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:32,000
Please take note, the front page template will display your site's homepage whether it is set to display latest posts or a static homepage.

89
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,000
The front page template takes precedence over all templates.

90
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:45,000
And that's a wrap. I trust you feel more comfortable now distinguishing between your homepage display settings as well as the various templates that form part of your theme.

